Package: LLPv3
Title: Liverpool Lung Project (LLPv3) Lung Cancer Risk Model for ModelsCloud
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ramin", "Rezaeianzadeh", email = "raminrzn@student.ubc.ca",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("John K.", "Field", role = "ctb",
           comment = "Author of the original Liverpool Lung Project model"))
Description: A self-contained, dependency-free implementation of version 3 of the
    Liverpool Lung Project (LLPv3) risk model, which predicts the 5-year
    probability of lung cancer from age, sex, smoking duration, family history
    of lung cancer, prior pneumonia, asbestos exposure, and prior (non-lung)
    cancer (Field et al., Thorax, 2021, <doi:10.1136/thoraxjnl-2020-215158>).
    The age- and sex-specific baseline and the risk-factor coefficients were
    taken from the official Liverpool calculator and verified to reproduce it
    exactly. The package exposes both the vectorised model function llpv3() and
    the standard ModelsCloud prediction API (model_run(), get_sample_input(),
    get_default_input()) for interactive use in R or deployment as a hosted
    model on the ModelsCloud platform.
